        <instrument_host_desc>
 
  Instrument Host Overview
  ========================
  The Eight Color Asteroid Survey was carried out during the years
  1979-1983 at the University of Arizona using the 1.54m Catalina
  telescope and the 2.29m Steward telescope.  The instrument used was
  a two-channel photometer with a dichroic beam splitter, and either
  a Varian VPM-159A.12D (InGaAsP) detector or an RCA C31034-05 (GaAs)
  for the red channel and with an EMI 9789QB (bialkali photocathode)
  detector for the blue channel.

